{"questionId":"14627268","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the equation of the perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>[</mo><mi>CD</mi><mo>]</mo></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find gradient of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CD</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>gradient of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> therefore perpendicular gradient <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CD</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong> &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for substituting the gradient and midpoint into equation of line, provided further work is seen leading to a correct answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14627268","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.7a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the equation of the perpendicular bisector of [CD] is y=-3x+18.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}